cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of deep learning methods for the analysis of chest CT images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new end-to-end 3D deep convolutional neural net (DCNN) for solving nodule detection, false positive reduction, and nodule segmentation jointly in a multi-task fashion. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves extensive experiments on a large-scale dataset, which may also make it relevant to the category of cs.MS (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which may also make it relevant to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
